	 <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>24 threads, <a href=/quest.html?quest=976&mid=9802591736624&start=0>1</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;</td></tr></table></form><a id=fs8 href=/quest.html?quest=976>Root thread</a><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9802591736624></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9802591736624><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Quest Spoiler</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jan 23rd 2:15 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok i dont know how much of this info was given below but i completed the quest yesterday and want to help you all out a little.  Ok the dire wolf fur you can find off any dire wolf which are found in for sure Iceland Ocean (island with tower of Frozen Shadows), Eastern Waste (everywhere) and great Divide also.  The pelts are just like any other a comon drop.  Some are magic and no drop though.  You need ONE medium quality pelt.  After that you need to get the stones which can be found in Eastern Waste.  this is harder than gettin the pelt because they spawn on the ground usually in highly mob populated areas.  I being a rogue first got a camo so i could be invis and move fast but camo is unreliable and u have to go far in EW.  Once it breakes mobs are everywhere so your chances of aggroing a Rhino, Snow Derv, Dire Wolf, snow Cougar, Frost Giant, Snow Griffon, or Kodiak (alot different and meaner)are very high they all roam these lands are very dangerous.  I've been told these stones spawn in various areas.  Some that I know of are (-5342,-1504),(-6459,1081),(-7254,1830).  I've confirmed these two (-7413,1709), (-6911,1814), these are roughly where I got mine.  I say roughly because I've found that these loc's are not consistent.  They seem to appear in this general area.  These were the loc's I was told but when I got to the exact location nothing, so being the military genius I am i started a circluar sweep from this point and on my two confirmed I found the red colored stone on the group close to the given loc's.  Also one was real close to the loc I was given but I did not see it the first time.  I think is a triggered spawn when u get near it or maybe I just had good timing.  But the second time I went to the loc and stood there for 5 to 10 min and the mob traffic got real heavy..(thank god for Rogue Hide and Sneak).  Then I saw a stone appear about 20 feet away.  As a rogue i just gave up on the camo and used hide sneak.  It took longer but i didnt get attacked once.  I just waited til the mob traffic calmed down then i looted which broke my hide and then I hide again.  these are No Drop so becareful if in a group cause so is the Cloak.  Ok i took these to the shaman in the hut by the Tower of Frozen Shadows in Iceclad Ocean.  Becareful I got attacked by a dire wolf once over there by huts and anyone who has been to Iceland nows.  Not one NPC will help u...lol and the one zone has to giants guarding it..lol.  Ok anyway...he did not talk to me at all...goes now if he even speaks or if someone else tells you want to give him but i took a chance and gave him 2 stones and 1 pelt.  It said something like Ergrez took the item and sewed together clothing something like that.  Thats it and I thought I was robbed cause there wasno xp, faction or item on my cursor but when i looked in my inventory there it was.  So make sure u have a free slot.  and Wa La thats it.  Hoped I helped at least one person thanks.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
